<statement>
<p>The cost to take a taxi from the airport is a function of the distance driven.  A 5 mile taxi ride from the airport costs <dollar/>10.  The cost is <dollar/>19 for a 10 mile ride.</p>
<p>
<em>y</em> is the cost and <em>x</em> is number of miles.</p>
<p>
<em>a.</em> Write an equation to model the situation. <em>y</em> = <fillin characters="20" />
</p>
<p>
<em>b.</em> What is the <em>y</em>-intercept? <em>b</em> = <fillin characters="4" />  What does it represent? </p>
<p><ul label="circle"><li><p>It takes 5 miles to get home.</p></li> 
<li><p>The meter drop is <dollar/>1.80.</p></li> 
<li><p>You start at <dollar/>10</p></li> 
<li><p>The cost for getting into the cab is <dollar/>1.</p></li> 
</ul></p>
<p>
<em>c.</em> What is the slope? <em>m</em> = <fillin characters="4" />What does it represent? </p>
<p><ul label="circle"><li><p>You start at <dollar/>1</p></li> 
<li><p>It takes 5 miles to get home.</p></li> 
<li><p>The meter drop is <dollar/>1.</p></li> 
<li><p>It costs <dollar/>1.80 per mile.</p></li> 
</ul></p>
<p>
<em>d.</em> Graph the equation.</p><figure><image source="mom/8ae5d8d917078b86b322354c5e5e0db1.png" /></figure><p>
